Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe welcomed Vice President Mike Pence on his third visit to Japan. The visit comes ahead of the East Asia Summit and the APEC Economic Leaders Meeting, highlighting the strong bond between Japan and the United States. The leaders discussed regional issues, including North Korea, the economy, and other challenges, in order to reaffirm their close coordination. Pence expressed gratitude for Japan's hospitality and discussed the importance of the Japan-U.S. alliance in maintaining peace and prosperity in the Indo-Pacific. He also mentioned the upcoming bilateral trade agreement and the goal of denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula. Both leaders emphasized the friendship and shared values between their countries.